{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "79865cfb-8942-499a-a1e0-fe23e27b0725",
    "name": "DiscoveryCollection-BB-9218-OEX",
    "description": "This collection covers library related operations including creating libraries and managing team members within them through API in response to a discovery \\[BB-9218\\] OEX: Discovery for Creating a Content Library and Assigning Admin Roles via API in Open edX from Salesforce.\n\n**Base URL:** `{{base_url}}` **Authentication:** All requests require a JWT token passed as:\n\n```\nAuthorization: JWT {{jwt_token}}\n\n ```\n\n---\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n| --- | --- |\n| `base_url` | The base url is extracted and put sepparatly for reusability purpose, it can be merged to each request urls if prefered. |\n| `jwt_token` | During demonstration, the value of jwt_token is extracted from an active session in a browser. A combination of edx-jwt-cookie-header-payload and edx-jwt-cookie-signature is used to form a complete jwt_token by which requests will be allowed. |\n| `library_id` | Except when creating a new library record, all other api calls involve a specific library to wich you may add a new team member, modify role of a team member or other tasks. The library_id is a provided here as a parameter for reusability perposes only. |\n| `teammember` | When performing access management, we can use an existing user to demonstrate add a new team member, modify or remove team member. teammember is separatly provided as a setting for reusability purposes. |",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "52034910",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/52034910-79865cfb-8942-499a-a1e0-fe23e27b0725?source=collection_link"
  },
